title: The famous temple of city !
review: This famous temple has been an attraction for the devotes travelers / locals who come here with prayers on the lips .The temple Architect is typical North Indian subtle with the big court yard and the shrine which is a hub of activity . The temple timings are strictly followed .Generslly flowers and Tulasi are offers here .

title: South india touch
review: Rangji temple was very famous among Pushkar. The architecture of the temple was just like south India temple. Nice temple and beautiful campus. Must visit.

title: Awesome Temple
review: I would suggest everyone to go at this place.

title: Good South-India temple structure view
review: When you just enter to Pushkar, you can see this temple.

title: It's worth a visit.
review: It's a serene and a gorgeous Temple.

title: Abode of The Lord
review: In pushkar, some 12 kilometres from Ajmer is located the famous shrine of Lord Vishnu ji, the upbringer of the world and the Lord of Luxury and prosperity...the temple is externally decorated in the famous Dravidian style of architecture and the walls outside the sanctum Santorum depict  pictures from religious scriptures of Hindu religion..beautiful paintings...and of course...the ultimate view of Lord Vishnu...holding His royal court is simply mesmerising..a must visit place in pushkar...

title: Very different architecture
review: Rangji temple was beautiful and have different architecture. Campus was also big. Must visit it. Famous in this area.

title: Off limits.
review: The temple is very impressive.You may see ceremonies from the street with priests entering.

title: Must see.
review: This is the only authentic south Indian style temple in whole of Pushkar. Spacious, clean and serene atmosphere.

title: Rangji Temple Pushkar
review: This is the personal temple of the Bangur Cement Family and built about 40 years ago.

title: Beautiful architecture
review: Rangi Temple of pushkar Ajmer is beautiful temple. it's architecture is mind blowing .this temple is looks like south Indian temple.

title: Rangji temple
review: Rangji temple of Ajmer is beautiful temple this temple is built in South Indian style Temple must see location.

title: Average place for tourists
review: Average temple for tourists.

title: Most Popular Tourist Destination
review: I went to Rangji Temple. Rangji Temple is one of the very famous temples of Rajasthan in Pushkar. The temple is one of the most popular tourist destinations in this part of the country where followers come to pray and give homage to the deities of the temple. It is great place to go.

title: You can see quite a bit
review: A good temple, as I could see. But I couldn't see quite a bit – the entry for  foreigners is prohibited. Max. – you can look at the portal and even take a picture through the doorway usually open. But only so. It's a big pity, because here the obvious elements of design, characteristic of sacral architecture of, say, Tamil Nadu, peacefully coexist with typical Rajasthani corner turrets, forming a rather rare and original appearance.

title: Nice to see a S.Indian temple in North but check the timings
review: Nice place. Perumal or Lord Vishnu temple. You would feel u r in a South Indian temple and the priest also are from S. India. Opposite to the temple have good shops -handicrafts. Timing is 6-12 in morning and 7-9 in the evening.

title: beautiful tempe
review: this is very good and beautiful temple. i prayed here to god. little crowdy but worth visiting. peaceful temple

title: Beautiful Lord Vishnu temple in Pushkar
review: By the grace of God we found ourselves just in the front of the temple on our way back to the hotel after visiting the Pushkar Lake.We got to know that it is one of the popular Temple in Pushkar.It is beautiful clean and serene place.The architecture is typical south indian .There was some construction/renovation work going on,we were very pleased to visit the temple.It is worth a visit,and in front of the temple one can visit local handicraft shops for buying gifts for friends.

title: A PLACE OF SOLACE
review: Visited the temple on 28.12.2015 on way to Ajmer. The very old temple was having a huge rush of people from all faith of life.

title: South Indian Touch in Puskar
review: Well known temple of Lord Jagannath ji  having Maa Laxmi temple also enjoyed PRASAD and blessings of Maa Laxmi

title: Great...
review: It is one of the famous temple in Pushkar. Such a wonderful experience to visit here. Architecture of this temple was quite amazing. Clean and lovely place.

title: Vishnu Temple
review: I went to this temple and brahma temple in Pushkar. I had to literally run from brahma temple to this temple as they were almost 5-10 mins walking distance away and it was about to be closed in the afternoon when i was going to Vishnu temple. But finally got the glimpse. Nice experience.

title: Traditional temple
review: A South Indian architecture  Hindu  temple in north India. It is a quiet peaceful place. Recommended for its peaceful setting and beautiful architecture.

title: A typical South Indian Temple at Pushkar
review: This Rangji Temple is very famous in Pushkar for its looks and is visited by many tourists.  The temple is very typical of a South Indian Temple in terms of the way it has been constructed with place for parikramas.  The main diety is Lord Vishnu.  It also also house to many other deities including Lord Ranganathji.  The temple opens early and closes by noon.

title: trip
review: it is very attractive temple and it is very good and very nice to see.it seems to be good and excited

title: Harry Krishna
review: Foreigners not welcome. I was lucky that I could take a photo.but I couldn't get inside even when I take off my shoes...!!

title: A south indian flavor - Vishnu Temple
review: Its nice temple with a different flavour and having sea sand...

title: The old temple for the  devotees
review: This temple is best known for the reason that over the years the generations of faithful devotees have been coming here to have glimpse of the Lord . This temple has the deity which is bewitching in the beauty . The morning / evening arti is the high light of the temple . The beautiful temple is synonymous with town and it's faithfuls. Must visit .

title: Clean, Calm and Disciplined
review: The overall experience at the temple was nice. It looks like temples from South India.

title: Foreigners not allowed in
review: It is a nice Temple from the outside but we were not permitted to enter the grounds to look around. It's a shame as we would have liked to.

title: Good!
review: The temple is nice. Its newly built so is clean and well maintained. Not a lot of people when we visited. One can spend some time easily sitting in the compound.

title: nice
review: In pushkar, a temple where you can find a south Indian kind of temple. sands and long open ground. evening aarti no to be missed.

title: Must visit
review: There are 2 (yes 2) Rangji temples at Pushkar. They are called the old Rangji and the new Rangji temples. Both are built by business families.

title: A nice visit but not a must do
review: I had been there just out of curiosity. It is like any other temple. Pleasant, divine and calm (atleast during the time I visited there). However, I did not find anything extra ordinary about this place and hence giving it a three star rating

title: The Only Temple for Brahma
review: We reached the place around sunset (Sayam Sandhya). There was a Puja for the Sarovar at Pushkar, similar to what you see for Ganga Aarti. Nearby place is the temple. Good unhurried place. Enjoy both atmosphere and Handicrafts of Rajasthan. Personal Transport goes almost to near the temple.

title: One of the temple must be visited when you are at Pushkar
review: The Brahma temple is the first religious place to visit at Pushkar because it is the only Brahma temple in the world but second is Rangaji temple which is so rich in architecture ,built in south indian style it is a beautiful temple,leather items and arms are not allowed-must see if you are in Pushkar for a trip-thanks-Sumer Singh Saran

title: Spiritual!!
review: As have mentioned by any other reviewer, it is the near to the only Brahma temple in the world, Would recommend if want to be in peace for a while!!

title: South Indian Style
review: Excellent Temple build  recently and the building style is similar  to south indian. Well maintained and neat and clean.

title: Venkateswara swamy temple-south indian style
review: Ranji temple is basically Venkateswara swamy temple. Its made in south indian style.very nice temple good to go

title: pushkar
review: the temple is situated just near to pushkar lake and have a peaceful ambiance. pl. take care of mandir timings while planning to visit rang ji mandir. nice place to visit...

title: A Temple of Lord Vishnu
review: Rangji Temple is also known as Sri Vaikunthnath Temple. The temple is dedicated to Sri Rangaji who is believed embodiment of Lord Vihnu.The temple is about 200 years old and was built by a south indian businessman of Ajmer. The architecture of the temple is remarkable as it is a perfect blend of South Indian, Rajput and Mughal style. A nice visit and Darshan.

title: Ranji temple
review: Authentically maintained strictly in sri vaishnava parampara, this temple is also known as Ranganathji temple of North. Loed Sriman Narayana and Lakshmi idols are divine. The sanctorium of ram, lakshman & janaki is nice and the temple also has Sudarshan swami sannathi. Dont miss this temple if you go to Pushkar or Ajmer

title: Beautiful place
review: Rangnathji temple is a temple of shri vaikuntnathji. A holy place in a holy atmosphere. must go and enjoy the blessings.

title: Nice temple
review: Its a nice temple with beautiful architecture. A little away from the main city and the main dargah, but worth a visit.

title: A tamil temple in Pushkar!!!
review: An unexpected Tamil Iyengar themed temple in Pushkar. Had to stand outside for half an hour in the blazing sun to get a darshan. Could certainly be managed better. It would be nice to have some concrete  info on the timings, this seemed to depend on the whim of the pandits. The pandits were discussing current affairs and cricket while giving teertham. However, the place was cleaner than many temples in the area and the environs were peaceful.

title: Southern touch in Puskar
review: must see temple with all pujari's in tradition of southern temples. large compound with enough space for large number of pilgrims to come at same time and have parikrama

title: New Rangji better managed than the old Rangji temple
review: There are two Rangji temples- the old is very ancient but the 'new' is also a heritage temple and very beautiful. It is relatively cleaner and better managed than the old one. Both the temples are a must to visit in Pushkar and can be combined with the visit to the Brahma temple

title: Good to visit but....
review: Great place to visit but be careful about the touts and the priest who try to fleece you by giving you fear and making you to sit in puja. Negotiate rates before hand otherswise very difficult to manage them afterwards.

title: "Beautiful Temple"
review: Lord Rangji is believed to be an incarnation of Lord Vishnu,very beautiful temple,beautiful architecture.Must visit this place.

title: We went to see place and worship
review: Its very beautiful place and good architecture , historical place attraction of tourist in pushkar ajmer

title: Peaceful and Great Architecture
review: A great architectural temple and one of a kind temple built in south Indian style of architecture.

title: Must Visit
review: Meet Mr. Ganeriwalji- Head of the Temple Trust. Absolute delight in Pushkar area. The Temple compound is a large area, needs some urgent renovation

title: Be sure of your time of visit
review: There are two Rangji temples, both close at 12m (noon) and reopen at 4pm.

title: Excellent traditional temple
review: The new temple is a typical perumal temple of south India. The campus is big and houses many of the priests. The pujas are traditional. Talking to the priests was nice. The temple closes around 12.15 PM and reopens at 4 PM. They offer prasads after the puja that included halwa, sundal and rice. Cameras, shoes and handbags not allowed inside.

title: Just Beautiful
review: Just Beautiful

title: Good Temple, need maintenance
review: Nice Temple, needs some maintenance. Its built in South Indian Style, you don't see many in northern india. It would be great if some maintenance work is done, currently it looks neglected.

title: what a temple
review: it spells of south Indian architecture and a real vast place,evening aarti is a must to be seen and assure you will remember ever.

title: Pushkar Mahotsav 2 was amazing
review: Pushkar Mahotsav was amazing in this temple.this place in in the market,can not take the car inside but in special case can be done by back entrance.The place can be converted into open air theatre and place is available for serving also.

title: South Indian Temple
review: Neat and clean and purely south indian design and poojas are perfomed by Iyengars of Tamilnadu. One must visit this temple and take the blessings of Lord Rangathji.

title: Magnificient
review: One Of the Oldest Temple in Pushkar is really a divine place and source of divine and spiritual energy. Evening Arti is something not to be missed
